Dinner will be stopped
Because dinner can be only served InFlight. 
After receiving the landingPermit, state will be Landing.
 There is no Dinner in Landing state

Initiall Aircraft is in an InHangar state. Then we prepare it for flight and  change state to Boarding.
Then after receiving takeoff permission the aircraft changes its state to TakeOff. After takeoff 
it changes its state to pullGearUp and after this it is getting back  to TakeOff state and then goes to InAir state.
While being in an InAir state the aircraft changes its state to flightControl. After receiving landing permisssion
the aircraft is changing its state to Landing. During landing the aircraft changes its state to pullGearDown.
After landing aircraft changes its state to Boarding.

Here we added TakeOff state, inside which we are at radioComm1 state while being on runway. 
After runway is freed the aircraft sends freeRunway signal.

Also we added Landing state, inside which we are at radioComm state during landing operations and while being on runway. 
After freeding the runway the aircraft sends freeRunway signal.

Here we elaborated InFlight state for long flights. Here if flight lasts more than 3 hours
we proceed to Dinner state, this state lasts for 1 hour. After that we leave InFlight state.

Here we created scenario for InFlight state, where our aircraft can be damaged. In case of
malfunction the Aircraft proceeds to Damaged state and after this 
we end InFLight state. If it is not damaged it proceeds
to  Normal state and changes its state to Landing.

Here we have simplified our diagram using submachine state. First: we have simplified the preparation for flight, we have placed the operations that correspond to landing in the submachine state LandingOps, 
and those that correspond to takeoff in the submachine state TakeOffOps. Operations that happen before InFlight state we put into PreInAirOps. Takeoff operations are also part of PreInAirOps, so we put 
them to PreInAirOps. 
Final diagram describes transitions between PreInAirOps, InAir state and LandingOps submachine state.
